 Fusion by 2037...</span><hr size=1> Fusion energy is more than likely possible.  The only thing really stopping it is the lack of political will to pursue it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 675<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/8/03 11:51:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bush Wants Fusion by 2037...</span><hr size=1> You'd think that with dwindling fossil fuel supplies and the increasing need for clean power worldwide that the powers that be would show a lot more interest in funding fusion research.  In the long run there would be greater benefits to funding research into fusion and other energy sources than to blow money on say the missile defense shield.  It's just amazing how our tax money is blown on projects that won't do anything for us in the long run or even the short term. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2856<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/9/03 8:49:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bush Wants Fusion by 2037...</span><hr size=1> Cough(<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>pipedream</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->).<br>
